dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yeah, it's pretty cool.  For example, if I hit DRAT in one stroke, then "Did there come a time" will appear in English on my machine's  LCD screen.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Wow that is crazy, I don't understand how that works, is it preprogrammed or does it go by how the word sounds?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Each stenographer has their own "Personal Dictionary" which is a list of words in English along with how you in particular write out those words or phrases in steno.  This dictionary is present within the actual steno machine after you transfer it from your laptop to the machine via cable or wifi.  Thus your machine then knows how you write out words in particular and how to translate those words from steno to English - each stenographer writes a little differently.

dialog.content: I made a mistake making California my home.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I'm sure it isn't, how long had you been together?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: California is beautiful I know, but it can also be pretty quick paced.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: We were together 10 years.  I am just disgusted that it had to happen at this point. Christmas week, of all weeks.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Are you still working?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I am still working right now.  Luckily, California has plenty of money for bureacrats lie myself.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I contributed to the marriage for sure.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I love my wife and my great kids

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It's important that you know that you can feel whatever way you need to about your loss. Its a tough time of year for something like that.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Had things been pretty rocky?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Things like this were sudden.  I mean, I never expected her to up and walk out with the kids.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: The only thing I can think of was that California was getting too expensive and the homeless were taking over LA; that may have spooked her to leave the state.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Wow, that's horrible. It seems you should have some kind of legal authority in that aspect.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Is that a big problem out there?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I really don't have any discourse.  The kids are almost 18.  They are twins. Yeah, in her eyes, she seems fed up with the state. She left me for Texas, the state, not the person.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I mean, she never mentioned loving, "Text," but the kids are bing into the Dallas Cowboys

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It is important that you understand that it seems that she has been thinking of this for a while.

violations.situation: I was dating this guy for about a month or so, and everything had been going well. It was my first relationship in a long time. All of a sudden, he ghosted me. No explanation. I was left thinking that I'm not built to be in a relationship.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I thought seriously about that, but for some stupid reason, I keep thinking, "What if he comes to his senses and wants to contact me?"

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: A couple months ago, but I haven't gotten over him.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: If you block him and he wants to get in touch, he will find a way.  Make him work hard

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: You really think playing hard to get will work?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I think if he is interested still it will, if not his loss.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Thanks for saying that, but I still have the problem of wanting to be in a relationship.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: With him, or a relationship with someone?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: With him... he was perfect (or at least I thought), but also, I'm lonely, and it's hard to process not being in a relationship during the pandemic.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Have you tried making other connections online? A lot of people are home during this pandemic, you may meet someone much better.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: True. What can I do to get over him in the meantime?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Keep busy! Get mad instead of sad!

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I would not contact him if he was not contacting me.  You deserve better than that!

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Lol. I think I can do that!

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Yes, we women function better when we get pissed!

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: You're right. What do I do if he contacts me again? Do I let the conversation play out and see what happens?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Play it cool and be ready to make up a whole bunch of fun things you have been doing.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: That's a good idea. I can do that.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Of course you can!

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: You may find your feelings have changed.  Sometimes we just want what we don't have, lol.

violations.situation: I had my heart set on a Veterinary Technology program at a particular school and I just found out that I won't be able to apply in time. I feel like I have to reassess my future plans.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: What are your interests/what do you like to do? Thats a good starting question

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Maybe another path involving animals. Either that, or something geared more toward counselling for humans, which is actually what I was interested in a long time before I decided on the veterinary route.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Okay! Well thats a good start I would continue looking in that.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Also if you miss working animals, you can always volunteer in a pet store.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Okay, I'll give it a shot.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: That's a great idea.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Do really like working with pets?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I do. I have a dog and I love her very much and want to be prepared if anything were to happen to her.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Also if you want to go into counseling, I'd recommend trying to get some practical experience to see if you like it.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Oh sweet I've always wanted a dog!

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yeah, mine is super awesome. She's a Presa Canario and just the sweetest and smartest.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Well it seems no matter what you can't go wrong. Do you want to talk about anything else?

violations.situation: I just was told that I ma out of a job as of January 15th.  I am going to get paid for those two weeks in January that I won't be with the company.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I understand,  I have been in a similar situation recently. COVID-19 really has got us all down.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: What a great nation we live in.....a future 3rd world one.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yeah, but I was a good accountant.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: WOW, I'm sure that is a big change for you...

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yeah, I have not told my wife about it just yet.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I agree, this country has got some issues but we can get through them

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Uh, oh, how do you think she will react?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yeah, I am not sure.  I better wait to break the news in 2021.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: The good news is that we are on an incline for unemployment so there are a lot of opportunities out there.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: And I am not the only one who is losing my job. Seems that all of accounting is going to be getting the axe. It makes me sad....

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: You could maybe tell her at the very end of this year so you can start fresh for the new year. Do you have a resume?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Plus, I have a 50 dollar a day spending habit on lottery tickets to one day hit it BIG

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes, I have a resume that I have not updated just yet.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I have a college education and a CPA to boot, but I need one lucky break in life.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Sometimes that will help to get a better perspective on things... taking some time away from everything in order to catch a breath.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Maybe I can spend some quality time with my kids without them knowing I will be out of a job as of 01/15/2021

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: It is almost Christmas, too.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I hear ya, I feel like that quite a bit. Like if isn't one thing it's another. I'm sure your wife will understand how the economy has gotten and that she knows that it isn't your fault.

violations.situation: My mom is stuck in Mexico and I hate she keeps asking me for money.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content:
Instead they suggested I should provide extra financial security
 to myself or at least some future children.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Grandma already is giving a home and 2 apartments but... I guess I am the only kid. Christ.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: My mom lost my om over 100k to be honest. It was crazy growing up to that

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It may be nice to have a bonus house for the future. But even that comes with headaches. In the end you have to do what is best for you.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yeah. I guess boundaries are good.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content:
I left her without much help to be honest but I guess just hearing it frustrates
 the crap out of me.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Or sell it now and pocket the money to recoup what was lost.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I would but it isn't even my property

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: And mom needs a place to stay... sometimes I wonder if she just wants to be homeless

dialog.content: So she is just talking circles and not accomplishing what she says?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: More like she keeps talking about doing something crazy like have a police chase

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: and how she doesn't care for anything

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Some people do choose that life to be free of responsibility.

dialog.content: Can you help me

dialog.content: Yes.

dialog.speaker: seeker

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Hi...

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: hello how are

dialog.content: you

dialog.content: what is the problem bud?

violations.situation: Finals week has pushed me to my limits and is causing me to be very stressed and moody.  Many people in my family are noticing my personality being like a stir-crazy animal.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: It is final's week and I am under a Helluvah lot of stress.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: School work is just pounding my brain.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I am taking 5 courses this semester, too.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I can definetely imagine how stressful the last week of school can be, especially taking 5 courses instead of 4.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: However, don't let this situation scare you or ruin  your holidays. There are ways to cope with said stress.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yeah.  I am glad you are here to help me think things through.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I need to find a solution to my anxiety while I knock out paper after paper.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: First of all, do you have some academic counselor you can talk to? Help you organize your ideas or classwork? Can you refer to professors or fellow classmates for help?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Well, counselors are hard to get ahold of so close to the Holidays.  The so-called teachers are not that helpful.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: seniors must figure it out by themselves.....(for the most part).

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: My roommate is a lunatic.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Are you confident in your abilities to succeed in those classes or you think you might lack the materials or knowledge? Or perhaps time?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I just don't know.  I am going to try my best to submit every assignment on time, even though the quality prolly won't be 100%.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I am a perfectionist by nature.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I am a bit moody and my roommates have noticed it.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It's okto be moody given the circumstances and the stress you are going through, and I think that you should attemp to complete all the assignments even if you don't get a 100% on them.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That will show the professors that you are responsible and care about the subject or perhaps your major.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I think that I need to research more to ace this out.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Accomplishing to submit everything will also make you feel good with yourself!

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It's important than you take your time.

violations.situation: Car accident led to traumatic brain injury and PTSD having nightmares 2x a week.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I have a traumatic brain injury that creates a lot of overstimulation in my life. I used to be social and now I can't be in a social setting for too long without feeling exhausted

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Have you tried to talk to your therapist through video chat or is that something they offer?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes, I talk to my therapist every other week

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That's great that they can offer that, I know it's very difficult to get regular care at the moment with the pandemic.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Do you have any family or friends close by or something that you can talk to if you feel like you need some extra support?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I do not have supportive or understanding friends and family

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I have lost a lot of them in the last few years or have created boundaries because when I got into my first car accident, legit someone said "are you not better yet?" and another said "can't you just walk it off?"

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: When I got into my second car accident, people said "again? are you drunk?"

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Even though neither were my fault, people were not understanding or asked how scary those situations for me were

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I am sorry to hear that, people are very quick to judge so it's very unfortunate that you were treated that way.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: After my first car accident, the tow truck guy was towing my car to my aunt's garage to hold for auto insurance appraisal. He said to my aunt "sorry for your loss" My aunt said "oh, she's right over there and alive"

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: the car accident was so bad the tow truck guy thought I had died

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: but even after seeing my car, friends and family acted like it was just something that happens to everyone. walk it off

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Wow, I can't imagine what the car must have looked like then for such a comment to be made. I'm glad that you here and despite going through that trauma that you are still going.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Why?

dialog.content: My supervisor said she would be in to help cover people on PTO and she never showed.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: yes

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Did anybody ever get in contact with her and to see why she never showed up?

dialog.content: Yes, she said she decided she was also taking PTO.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Even though she had already said she would help cover.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I understand how you are feeling because i would be angry to

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I feel like she should of let everyone know that before she decided to do that

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Agreed, but at this point I just need to get over it so I can help pick up the slack.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: But i'm just so upset.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Have you personally had a conversation with her and tell her how you was feeling?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: No, i'm afraid to bring it up.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Don't be afraid to bring it up because you did nothing wrong

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That would be an absolutely terrible thing to do. Do you really think that your friend would do a t hing like that to you?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I have seen Rick eyeballing my girl at times.  I think he is an agressive guy when it comes to the ladies.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Rick thinks that he is a "playah."

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Do you think that perhaps you should talk to him before anything happens? You do not want to ruin your friendship by having him do that

dialog.content: I see - that is interesting, I have never heard of anything like that before. Do you think that there might be some sort of physical problem going on?

dialog.content: I hear  you saying that they are not really effective, is that true?

dialog.speaker: seeker

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: so, yea

dialog.content: Okay .. I hope you reported him!!

dialog.content: Dogs are very very loyal. They never cheat on you or walk out on you!

dialog.content: Alright, bud. Thanks. You, too

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: take care!

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: (you need to quit first and take the survey .. I can't :))

violations.situation: I don't like any of my friends. In fact, I don't think I like anyone.

dialog.content: a long time. more as i age. i'm actually tired about hearing about the pandemic, really. it is all people ever talk about.

dialog.content: more people are probably dying of obesity

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: eating themselves to death

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: People like that are irritating, certainly. I am not sure what the solution is, other than to ignore them.

violations.situation: Quarantine keeps going on and on.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I can definetely understand why. During this pandemic we have been more isolated than ever

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It's not easy

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I mean it's one thing to limit capacities in places, but to say we're not allowed to go to our friends' and family's home is just plain ridiculous.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It is more than reasonable to be frustrated with regards to that. I myself have not been able to visit my ill mother. She lives in another country, so it's especially difficult.

Instead of laughing or jumping with fright in theaters with everyone, we now have to do it with ourselves. Rather than cheering as an audience over a touchdown, it's now a crowd of one. It just feels robotic now.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I agree with you, what used to be super-exciting activities now have a much more monotonous feeling.

dialog.speaker: supporter

oh that is quite a pile of conflict on you. you must be feeling emotionally

Stuff about how she didn't post on social media about her birthday, and little petty things like that. Not something an adult should be concerned with. And I still sat and listened to her all that time.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I completely understand how unappreciated and stressed this would make you or any person. Especially when our plate is full and its the same old same old and nothing is changing. Its like thinking doing same thing over and over you will get a different result when 2+2 equals 4

dialog.speaker: supporter

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: However, it is time to take the hard road. YOu are going to have to say with LOVE because its not always what you say but how you say it.  Give me a minute to please type it

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Okay, thank you.

dialog.speaker: supporter

I have always been there for you but you are not willing to take my advice or others advice and quite frankly I just can't do it anymore. IF you want to remain friends I need you to grow up and realize the world doesn't revolve around you or even me.  Right now I could really use a good friend. I am going thru A LOT OF Sh** and I don't need this in my life. So

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: if you aren't able to do that than I am afraid until you can be a true friend and not just a user than I need to end this friendship . I don't want to but I need to for my mental health and for myself and even for you.  I say this because I love you and I do care but this has become toxic

dialog.speaker: supporter

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Hmm, has he been looking for work, or just laying around playing video games and shit like that?

dialog.speaker: seeker

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Well, I suppose it's possible that he's been earnestly looking and just not having any luck.  Is he kind of a loser in general, or is he a stand-up guy?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: He got average grades in school but didn't really miss days from school.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Ok, so it sounds like you're kind of fed up with him in general, and not having a job is maybe just a part of the bigger issue?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: That's probably correct.  He hasn't been in contact with me as much since I left for school.  I just expected more.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Well,  it sounds like you're both in kind of a transitional period in life.  It's pretty normal for relationships to not necessarily survive through things like this

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: That's so sad since we have so many years together, but I feel like I'm moving forward and he is staying in place.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Yeah, I mean it's never easy going through a breakup, but people change as they get older and mature, and they aren't necessarily going to still be compatible the whole time.   Also I think it's important to not think of a relationship that peters out as a failed one.   Just because it didn't last until one of you died doesn't mean it wasn't a success.   I think people put too much emphasis on permanence.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: That's true, it can maybe just be a stepping stone to build other relationships.  Thanks for the wisdom.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Well I've got a couple decades on you, so I've been through this a few times before.   Actually I'm still friends with pretty much all of my exes.   I mean just because I'm not romantically involved with them anymore doesn't mean that they aren't still terrific people.   Hell, I hung out with two of them just today.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: That's great you have maintained positive relationships and were also able to move  forward.  Thanks for the advice. I appreciate it.

dialog.speaker: supporter

And I agree. The longer we put it off and don't take it seriously,

dialog.speaker: supporter

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content:
Like I said the question has arisen more than once. The first time he owned to talking to other women, but nothing more.

Since that time, he denies everything.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Honestly, its not anyone else's business. IF you're suspicions are in fact correct, then you've got to see that a loving and faithful 5 is better than a heart-breaking 10. However should you find that maybe the devils of insecurities are tricking you into thinking that she's cheating, then remember that what the two of you share o=is FOR THE TWO of you. Its a relationship, not a community project! Even mu advice, albeit in the air to help you best I can. is not more important that what matters most to YOU and HER!

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Curiously, why do you think she's cheating?

dialog.speaker: seeker

She goes away with work and when she does she rarely messages me. Recently she said when was going way for a work trip for three nights but when I called her office her colleague said they got back after two.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Hmm... So have you two live together?  How long has this kind of behavior persisted? When you ask her about this behavior, how do you present the question and how does she react? Finally, how often do you talk with her about the situation?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Don't get me wrong, I completely understand why you have suspicions. Really I think anyone would in the same shoes... However, as humans, we tend to either assume the best or the worst of others. There's always a margin of error present as a variable in such situations.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Forgive me if this comes off as disrespectful... I only want to help you.

dialog.speaker: supporter

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I would agree that the relationship is getting a bit toxic but before terminating such a long relationship i would do one thing. dialog.speaker: seeker

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Yeah to be honest if you press the issue and ask if anything is going and you continue to get toxic responses. It might be time to end the friendship. I would do that as a last resort but there is no need for you to be carrying it one sided and holding all the burden as well. It hurts to have to end a long friendship but unfortunately sometimes it has to happen to keep yourself in a better spot.

dialog.speaker: supporter

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Ooh, yeah. I like your ringtone idea too! I usually make it some sort of song that I like and then end up either sleeping past it or not hearing, but I think making it something loud or annoying would really help to get me up to turn it off.

dialog.speaker: supporter

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: If any, you can try exercising whenever possible because it's goof for your health. However, do not let the comments about your appearance affects you.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: yeas , but sometimes we feel bad  right when own people doing those comments hurts more

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I understand, especially if that's someone close to you

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: yea will do slowly and thanks dear for so much concern on me

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: true , we wish our own people should understand our situation and help us to come over the problem

dialog.speaker: supporter

violations.situation: My job contract is ending in another month but I was informed that I would be let go and the contract would not be renewed. I am very anxious

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: But I tried negotiating. They are down-sizing the entire sales department. What else can I do?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Hmmm, I can see that this is stressful for you

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Did you already search for a new job?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes I am preparing my resume but job vacancies are few and far between. I am worried about my next job.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Okay then, It's good that you already started

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: But first of all stop being panicked

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Ok. Do you have any ideas for sales positions?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Search online and locally, get help from your friends and I assure you if you try hard enough you will suceed

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I will. How can I get help from friends? Only very few are in sales field.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: And remember, what are we if we stop fighting?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Your friends can support you emotionally at least and maybe they know a person that could help you

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I agree. I should never give up. But due to financial commitments, I am somewhat afraid of failing.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Life is full of surprises, but we should get advantage of bad situations

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It's totally fine to be afraid, but also at the same time     you should try harder to reach your goal

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes, so far life has been kind to me even if it surprised me at few places! I will try to make the most of the situation.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: You are right! Hard work will pay. I need to pull my socks up...

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Courage is not the absence of the fear, you should fight to find your place

violations.situation: I am dealing with a COVID-19 quarantining situation. Can't interact with family and friends. Wife is super paranoid about the virus.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Can't see friends, family, hug grandkids...

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That is extremely understandable.  The pandemic is an event no one was prepared for, and it has cause unforseen upheavals.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That is a tough situation, being isolated physically from those that you love.  I'm sorry you're going through that.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: It's been going on for months with no end in sight

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Are you at least able to maintain contact through text and video chats?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: How do you deal with it?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes, some video chats, but not the same

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Well, I make sure I continue to maintain my relationships as well as possible through the avenues I have available.  It is definitely not the same, but it's what we have at the moment.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Personally, I try to maintain a routine.  First hour after I wake up is coffee time, coffee and social media scroll time

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Then there is my wife. She is very paranoid about the virus

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: She sanitizes the house even though no one comes in it. Bitches at me.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That sounds very stressful, I'm sorry to hear that.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I appreciate your concern. It helps to have someone to vent to.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Is this going to end soon???

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I definitely cannot answer that.  As long as people keep valuing one another though, we will get through it.

violations.situation: I am living with a controlling mentally abusive husband

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Hi! I am feeling down and upset

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: CAN YOU FIND ONE POSITIVE THING THAT HAPPENED TODAY?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: No! I keep hearing the negative cruel remarks being repeated in my head over and over

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: WHAT DO YOU HEAR?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Also, you typing in all caps consistenly makes it feel like you are yelling at me

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: How I am worst than a pig. I am white trash! Even pigs are cleaner than I am . I am worthless

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I apologize I broke my hand and its easier for me.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Ok no worries . I am so sorry. Please continue in caps. I just sprained my left thumb and wore a splint

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: It was so difficult and painful so ignore my comment

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I am sorry that the world has hurtful people. are these people who can be avoided?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: No I currently live with him. My ex was way worst

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Can you get away from this situation? I have resources that could help you.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I have two boys and he said if I left him I would never see kids again.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: we can get the kids to safety as well

violations.situation: overall daily stresses

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I understand; sometimes I have moments like that, too.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: like time is moving on so quickly and there's so little hours in the day but I feel that I don't do enough in a day with my school, kind of distracted or wasted time and then when I do something, I look at the time and am sometimes surprised at how much time had actually elapsed when it felt like I didn't do much.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: What kind of things are you doing for yourself?  Do you have a place to or a thing to do to...decompress?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I think this has to do with the pandemic at the start of the year and that changed my momentum and rhythm in life and coupled with social isolation, which puts a damper on my studying mentality, I think.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I spend tons of time at home nowadays. I try to surf the net and read up on stuff, and that takes a lot of my time, and kind of aimless, and what I would say is procrastination. I work out from time to time, but not as much as I used to before the pandemic.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Sure, it sometimes feels like time is different right now.   Like your typical life patterns just did a complete circle.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I wanted to set aside hobbies and things to develop, like writing during the pandemic, and improve on that skill, but I never got to do that. And now so many months have gone by, and all that's on my mind and plate now are my studies, because it's like I do things slower and leave it till the last minute, even though I know I can pass, but just not as good a mark as I would have liked and not my usual work and study ethics from before.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: yeah not only a complete circle but to me, it's like an aimless road to nowhere, and it goes on and on and repeats day after day

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: that's how it felt for the last few months

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: and everyday is the same and at home, and only two months ago I started working in a new part-time position and that got some normalcy back and less stress and alleviated unpredictability with the economy for me.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Understood!  I'm not in the exact same situation, but I feel you.  There's the thought there would be so much to do things and...there's not.   And you feel stuck a bit.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: stuck for sure. It still amazes me that it's november and not march, because it still feels like that.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: and nowhere as festive, fun, and alive as last november. It's a huge change

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Definitely a massive change!

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content:
it feels nothing special, and not normal, and not even like a real november, you know? It's like even if it's christmas, I wouldn't ackowledge it's christmas even though it is, because of the changes and we can't do the things w
e used to do.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: hopefully, scientists can study all these phenomena and our physiological, social, and mental responses to the pandemic. There will be so much that can be learned from all this, I feel.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Of course.    We can'r celebrate the way we used to, we might not be able to visit family.   Oh yes, this is a learning opportunity about anxiety and isolation

violations.situation: Haven't been able to find a companion for years, loneliness has driven me to depression.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It sounds like you feel your friends are too busy for you.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes, but the biggest part is not being able to find romantic partner.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Why do you think you are having trouble finding a suitable romantic partner?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Part because of my low income and part because of my age. I live in a college town and most single women are 10 years younger than me.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Sometimes meeting people through mutual friends is helpful. Have you asked any of your friends if they could introduce to you people they know?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I've tried but my friends don't have very large social circles and most mutuals are already dating or are not interested in dating anyone at all.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I can see how that would make it difficult. What about internet dating or going to a single's night?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I am sure if you get yourself out there, you will definitely meet a great partner for you.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Internet dating is a cost issue, the most popular apps charge to meet the person, I could look at singles nights once the Covid issue is over. I don't even know if there are any locally.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It seems Covid is making dating difficult for everyone.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I hear that from people. I wish I had Covid as an excuse instead of just being confused about why I can't find someone.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It is reasonable to use Covid as an excuse. I am sure there are plenty of women out there who are also confused about why they can't find someone.

violations.situation: My boyfriend and I went on separate vacations with our friends, and he cheated on me while he was away.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Has someone cheated on you?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Luckily I have never been in that situation but my friends have

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: It never happened to me before.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I feel betrayed.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: But trust me, you made the right decision. If anything, it proves you're a strong and independent person

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Maybe I'll just go home for the holiday season.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: People can only love and respect you when you treat yourself that way

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That's a great idea! Spend time with your friends and family, who actually care about you and your feelings

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I wanted to throw something at him, I was so mad. But I just made him leave.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: You are very mature. Anyone in that situation would feel the same.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Thank you. It was hard not to let my emotions get the best of me. I don't even know why he told me. But I guess it's good he did.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: He did a good thing at least, being honest with you. However, cheating, even just once, is something I always warn people

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I don't know if it was good. Maybe he was just being mean.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: It's nice of you to listen. Thank you for all your advice.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: i hope I can travel home safely now.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: And maybe come back in January.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I know it's useless to tell you to not be sad. Go ahead and let it all out by crying or screaming but please know you didn't do anything wrong

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I hope I can be help

violations.situation: I recently found out that my best friend has lied to me about her whole life, and when I invited to my home she finally told me the truth after staying for a month ad we were fighting for the entire month she stayed.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That's definitely very upsetting. I know how it feels to have that sense of betrayal from a friend I was close to for many years. However, I was able to discuss the issue I had with my parents and other friends. Do you have anyone else close to you that you can talk to?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I don't think so, my parents think I was too harsh by deciding to end the friendship, it as if my own family doesn't understand.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That can definitely add to frustration. What about your other friends? Do you have anyone who either shares the same opinion as you or does not know your friend that you can talk to?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: My other friend believed that it wasn't too harsh to end the friendship as they know I value honesty but it makes me feel angry that I was being used for so long and constantly lied to.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: You have every right to be angry, but the most important thing you can do is find a good support system with your other friend. It will take some time to heal, but I'll tell you a paraphrased version of one of my favorite quotes: "Resentment is like swallowing poison and expecting the other person to die." It's important to find support in your other friends and heal properly.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I really love that quote, it's absolutely true; I think I will talk to my friend about the situation some more so I can fully get over it.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That sounds like a wonderful idea. Is there anything else you would like to discuss?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes, I also realized that I wasn't angry with my friend but rather myself

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Can you elaborate more? Earlier you said you and your friend were arguing while she was living in your house, then she stopped talking to you. Why might you be angry with yourself?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Because I basically allowed her to use me for seven years and kept lying to me or gave her space because I thought I was being a good friend.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I feel like I was stupid to do that and soft

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: If I may, I would argue that your actions don't make you soft and they certainly don't make you stupid. They are certainly not any reason to be angry with yourself. If I may bring up another clich: "Fool me once, shame on you. Fool me twice, shame on me." I would say you're in the "fool me once" stage and it is your friend's actions that have brought you pain. I think you're unlikely to trust her again.

violations.situation: related to the current pandemic

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: We won't know more about the mental implications and the sociological aspects of the pandemic probably until years to come.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I thought about that

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Yeah, and that just throws on another layer of why things are difficult right now. No one wants to feel guilty for doing things that could help themselves.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: to the gym, I certainly would. Because it's indoors and I do feel it's unsafe as there are many equipment that others could touch. Running I felt that way because the path that I usually run on is narrow and other people walk through it also. However, I did have second thoughts about that when the case numbers were down. But I finally decided to keep doing it and stick to all outdoor trips for essential business.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: but that's just me, and I know we all have different personalities, preferences, and tolerances of risks and acceptances, etc.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Have you ever heard of the phrase "black or white thinking?" As in, thinking that situations or people are completely good or completely bad? Or completely doable or completely impossible?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: so in my opinion, I feel a little indignant at the people that have been going out frivolously like there's nothing going on, to even gamble their safety and their family's. Like I live in an apartment building, and the people around me and below me are always going out, even for the last few months. So I don't feel safe either but also indignant that others are doing what I could have done, but that I had compromised on for my safety and everyone else's safety. So I just didn't feel it was fair for them to do that when I could have done that anytime I wanted.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: black and white thinking...let me think

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: for this pandemic, it's pretty much black and white

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Yeah, I think I understand that too. I get really frustrated hearing about people hosting big parties or not wearing masks because they think it's no big deal. They're putting others at risk.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Because I either go out or I don't. I have to compromise my values and everything I worked hard to preserve for the last few months to go out, even if I put on extra protection etc. And I just rigidly refuse to compromise my values because I don't believe it's right. Because if I had done that, I would have done that already, and long ago. And even though it's really hard on me.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: yeah exactly. Because people are being selfish and are subjecting others to risks even if they don't care about themselves.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: but I know I am pretty extreme in my thinking.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I really love the outdoors and I go out pretty often before the pandemic.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: But it's just that my own thinking is rigid and made up about it.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: But anyhow, that's the situation in a nutshell.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I think we all do black-or-white thinking to some extent. We're wired to try and make sense of the world, and maybe our brains don't like to spend time on nuance and grey areas. We all tend to quickly categorize things into good or bad, easy or hard, black or white.

violations.situation: I used to love my field of study, But soon after entering the university I started skipping the classes and failing. I lost my interest and there was nothing to motivate me.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Hi

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I had problems in the past and somehow right now

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: What sort of problems were in your past and now?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I loved physics and I decided to attend university, but soon after I slowly lost my interest and became unmotivated

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: What was happening in your life that made you lose interest?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Actually the professors and the class atmosphere was the reason, and of course the quality of teaching

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: so I started to skipping the classes and failing

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It sounds like that is a lot of reasons to be stressed. Have you spoken to a school counselor?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes lots of stress and pressure. I did not, because we didn't have such things or at least I wasn't aware

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: But nobody even pointed that why I'm failing, they just didn't care

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I agree it is a lot of pressure, but do not let bad teachers deter you. I would reach out to a school counselor and let them know your situation. Every school must have one.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Also, physics is a difficult course to study, but if you chose it, that means you have a very strong mind.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I loved physics a lot more than now, but what's the point of studying when the teachers are pulsing you not to study! (because of the quality of teaching)

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I hope there was someone, but I don't think we have a counselor

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: More reason to speak to a school counselor or school administrator. We need to provide help to students, not have bad teachers deter them.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yeah, same with me! I wish I could attend a better univeristy

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: What made you choose this particular university you are at?

violations.situation: I am in the process of applying to colleges and my parents are making a big deal of getting into the school of their choice. If I do not, it is up to me to find a way to pay for college.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: yes. tell me what happened?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I am very stressed. My parents want to me to go to the school of their choice but its not looking good. If I dont go into their choice school I will have to pay for school on my own.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Im not able to complete my work at school becuase of the stres

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: it sounds that you dont feel heard by your parents.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes, they just tell me they want the best for me but its making my stomach hurt constantly

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: i think you have done your best and you are continuing to try hard.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: i think you have done your best and you are continuing to try hard.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Thank you. I just don't know what I should do about my school and future college endeavors

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: everything happens  for a reason. you just have to stay calm.did you express yourself to your friends or a caretaker?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: My friends just tell me to take loans out like they are.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: do you think that will help you out?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I think it would but I don't want to go into debt because of college

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: try do get some online jobs so that you can cop up with both your college and finances.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Okay I can try and do that

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: yes, i hope everything ends well.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Thank you

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: welcome

violations.situation: I found out my partner was cheating on me and I just feel betrayed and heartbroken.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I feel like shit and I don't know how I can move on.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I can't help but feel there must be something wrong with me, or if I did something wrong.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It sound like you are having a really hard time right now.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Like I had all these plans and they just came crashing down, and now I have to start all over again.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Well yeah, I just broke up with my partner after finding out they cheated on me.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: That is a very difficult situation. Starting over again can be a great opportunity for growth.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I feel like I'm too old to start over again. There must be something wrong with me after all.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I understand how you feel. I had a bad break up, but it turned out to be a good thing in the long run.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: How so?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Well, looking back the relationship was pretty toxic and everything was better once I was out of it. I am sure your life will be happier and more fulfilling soon.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It sounds like you are blaming yourself for everything. Why do you feel at fault?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I don't know, it doesn't feel like anything's getting better soon. I've been busy with work so I haven't been spending as much time with my partner.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: It sounds to me like you have been working hard to support your life with you partner. They should respect that.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Maybe it is my fault, maybe I didn't communicate enough.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Is this a relationship you would want back if you could get it back?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: No, I don't think I'd want to get back with someone who cheated on me.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I would agree with you on that! That was how I felt too.

violations.situation: I asked my friend if she would go to the store with me because I was feeling down and overwhelmed with kids. She said she was too tired so she would have to pass this time. I was angry because I always support her when she is down or needs it. When I need it, she is nowhere to be seen. It's okay I guess for her to be depressed, but no one else can, because she has already monopolized that emotion. How can you ask someone for help when you are feeling depressed when they are depressed themselves?

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I am sorry to hear that sounds like she sure could use some help as well. Have you tried first taking about her issues and then telling her about yours?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I talk about her issues constantly. I guess I could do a better job about letting her know when I am feeling down. I just ask her to do things with me instead, but maybe she just takes it at face value. Literally everytime we talk though, it's about her problems.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: But she never does anything to try and fix them.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I am sorry to her that, so it sounds like you feel you need to give her help but you dont get any from her. But is also sounds like she might not be aware of you needing help.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes, exactly.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: It would be nice if I didn't have to explicitly spell it out. It makes it seem less meaningful when I have to spoonfeed to her what is wrong and what I need her to do for me.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I think you need to try to tell her about your problems, and maybe even if she feels like she is helping you she is more inclined to help herself some too?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: That's true, I didn't think about that really. Helping others def can help to take the focus off of yourself.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I know, it would be nice of her to ask how are you? But maybe she thinks you are a very strong person that does not need help since you do not voice it.?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yeah, that is true. I guess I am not looking at it from her persepctive.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Yes the feeling that you help someone can be uplifting and good for anyones ego

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Should I tell her that I am frustrated with her lack of helping me or just try to put that behind me?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: What is a good way to broach that I need help. Like I guess I don't know how to bring it up organically in a conversation

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I would try to find a conversation and then tell her like sometimes I could use help with whatever and then tell her that you feel lonely and need her sometimes as well

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Okay, I can try that. I guess I get so caught up in the frustration and my expectations of her, that I don't give it a chance.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Give it a try and you are not alone as you see we had a nice conversation.

violations.situation: My friend borrowed money from me and she did not return it in the time that we agreed.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Have you talked to them about the money and returning it?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes,i am very very upset.What would you do in my position?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Yes,she just sounded non-comittal,saying that she will return it when she can

dialog.speaker: supporter

violations.situation: When I broke up with my boyfriend of 5.5 years, I felt extreme fear. Fear of the unknown and fear of what was to come. We shared so much of each other's lives, I didn't know how to go on without him.

dialog.speaker: supporter

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I can understand your feelings right now, It's hard to ignore all those memories and moments

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: What bothers you the most? living alone or not having him?

dialog.speaker: seeker

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: Probably living alone and being on my own.

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: I don't really miss him honestly. I miss the comfort of having someone take care of me. We fell out of love awhile ago.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Hmm, First of all stop being scared

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: You can do it on your own

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: I know that's scary for you, but what's the meaning of life without being scared and have our feelings?

dialog.speaker: seeker
dialog.content: That's very true. I have to think about the future. I can do it on my own. I just have to think...this is the worst it'll ever be.

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: But you should start to take control over your feelings at first, you are the boss and you give the orders!

dialog.speaker: supporter
dialog.content: Slowly but surely you find yourself in a better mood

dialog.content: You said you felt relieved, and that's an opportunity

dialog.speaker: seeker
